thread.title: Hong Kong Pro-Democracy Candidate Barred From Election

author: wsjcom
title: Hong Kong Pro-Democracy Candidate Barred From Election
text:
A candidate from a pro-democracy party has been barred from running in Hong Kong’s election in March, further dashing the political ambitions of a group of young people whose advocacy stems from mass protests in the city.
In the latest stumbling block for the embattled Demosisto party, its nominee for the city’s Legislative Council, 21-year-old Agnes Chow, was disqualified, the party said.
